[ProMED-mail thanks Dr. Alan Tice for his contribution. This comment
from Dr. Tice is in response to a recent ProMED-mail post on an
outbreak of community-associated methicillin-resistant _Staphylococcus
aureus_ (CA-MRSA) infection in open ocean rowers (Staph. aureus
(MRSA), comm acq - Canada: (BC) rower 20110812.2452).

At least 9 of the 14 crew members who participated in this
transatlantic rowing expedition developed extensive furuncles and
carbuncles, and 3 of the 9 required hospitalization. One woman rower
developed disseminated CA-MRSA infection with multi-organ failure
several months after the rowing expedition. Secondary transmission
also occurred among household members. - Mod.ML]
